cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.RO, cs.MM 

The paper deals with computer vision and machine learning techniques for multi-person tracking and activity recognition. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also uses graphical models and Bayesian frameworks, which are common in the sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also deals with tracking and recognition of pedestrian actors, which falls under the sub-category of cs.RO (Robotics). Finally, the paper deals with hypergraph formulation, which is a common technique in the sub-category of cs.MM (Multimedia).
